1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE BILL 4355 By: Moore
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to police dogs; requiring certain law
enforcement agencies to equip vehicles used in canine
8 law enforcement programs with a heat alarm system
that activates under certain circumstances; providing
9 what the system must do when activated; providing for
codification; and providing an effective date.
10
11
12
BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 34-110 of Title 11, unless there
15
is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16
A. As used in this section, "law enforcement agency" shall mean
17
the police department of any municipality.
18
B. 1. A law enforcement agency shall equip each vehicle used
19
in a canine law enforcement program with a heat alarm system that is
20
activated when the vehicle stops running or the temperature in the
21
vehicle's interior exceeds eighty-five degrees (85°) Fahrenheit.
22
2. The system, when activated, must:
23
a. activate an audible alarm,
24
Req. No. 15625 Page 1

1 b. automatically lower the vehicle's rear windows, and
2 c. notify the canine law enforcement officer of the
3 dangerous situation.
4 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
5 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 566 of Title 19, unless there is
6 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
7 A. As used in this section, "law enforcement agency" shall mean
8 the police department of any county sheriff's department.
9 B. 1. A law enforcement agency shall equip each vehicle used
10 in a canine law enforcement program with a heat alarm system that is
11 activated when the vehicle stops running or the temperature in the
12 vehicle's interior exceeds eighty-five degrees (85°) Fahrenheit.
13 2. The system, when activated, must:
14 a. activate an audible alarm,
15 b. automatically lower the vehicle's rear windows, and
16 c. notify the canine law enforcement officer of the
17 dangerous situation.
18 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
19 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 9301 of Title 74, unless there
20 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
21 A. As used in this section, "law enforcement agency" shall mean
22 any police department with statewide jurisdiction as well as any
23 university or college campus police.
24
